{"expireTime":9007200830383581000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-ast-624385ce397a91dcbde421de081beed1-gatsby-remark-relative-imagesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-copy-linked-files-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Costa Rica is a nature-lover’s paradise — and it’s one of my favorite countries in the world too. It was the first country I ever traveled to and it was the country that sparked my wanderlust.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1,"offset":0},"end":{"line":1,"column":193,"offset":192}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1,"offset":0},"end":{"line":1,"column":193,"offset":192}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The beaches feel like paradise, there’s great surfing, diving, and plenty of places to get away from the hordes of retired Americans that live here. No matter what your interest, there are tons of things to see and do in Costa Rica without breaking the bank.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1,"offset":194},"end":{"line":3,"column":259,"offset":452}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1,"offset":194},"end":{"line":3,"column":259,"offset":452}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"But is Costa Rica safe to visit?","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":4,"offset":457},"end":{"line":5,"column":36,"offset":489}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1,"offset":454},"end":{"line":5,"column":36,"offset":489}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The country was fortunate to escape the Cold War conflicts and brutal gang violence that impacted other countries in Central America. However, in recent years, Costa Rica has become more involved in drug trafficking and money laundering.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":491},"end":{"line":7,"column":238,"offset":728}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":491},"end":{"line":7,"column":238,"offset":728}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 675px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/df07d02dd1f0d8c3894c399073fad7c3/48d16/c2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.51851851851851%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"c2\"\n        title=\"costa\"\n        src=\"/static/df07d02dd1f0d8c3894c399073fad7c3/48d16/c2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/df07d02dd1f0d8c3894c399073fad7c3/ab422/c2.jpg 512w,\n/static/df07d02dd1f0d8c3894c399073fad7c3/48d16/c2.jpg 675w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 675px) 100vw, 675px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":730},"end":{"line":9,"column":29,"offset":758}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":730},"end":{"line":9,"column":29,"offset":758}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Is Costa Rica Safe for Solo Travelers?","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":4,"offset":763},"end":{"line":11,"column":42,"offset":801}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":760},"end":{"line":11,"column":42,"offset":801}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Costa Rica is a safe country to visit for solo travelers. As long as you stay away from isolated areas, don’t wave your valuables around, and don’t travel alone at night you will be able to avoid the most common dangerous situations.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":803},"end":{"line":13,"column":234,"offset":1036}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":803},"end":{"line":13,"column":234,"offset":1036}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Additionally, be sure to download offline maps and an offline language app (like Google Translate) so you can look up directions if you get lost or communicate with the locals in an emergency. If you can, try to learn some Spanish before you go too. Even a few key phrases can go a long way!","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1038},"end":{"line":15,"column":292,"offset":1329}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1038},"end":{"line":15,"column":292,"offset":1329}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Is Costa Rica Safe for Solo Female Travelers?","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":4,"offset":1334},"end":{"line":17,"column":49,"offset":1379}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":1331},"end":{"line":17,"column":49,"offset":1379}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Costa Rica is one of the safest countries in Central America so if you’re new to solo female travel, Costa Rica is a great country to start with. However, you’ll still need to take some precautions of course. Always avoid isolated locations and don’t travel alone after dark. If you happen to experience cat calling or harassment from strangers on the street, be confident, avoid eye contact, and walk away.","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":1381},"end":{"line":19,"column":408,"offset":1788}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":1381},"end":{"line":19,"column":408,"offset":1788}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Solo female travelers will want to remain extra vigilant at bus terminals, bars, and taxi stands where harassment is more common. When traveling around the city, ask your hotel what the safest route is and also which areas you should avoid. Also, avoid taking taxis at night — especially by yourself.","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":1790},"end":{"line":21,"column":301,"offset":2090}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":1790},"end":{"line":21,"column":301,"offset":2090}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"By taking some precautions and planning accordingly, solo female travelers will be able to have a memorable time in Costa Rica. Just make sure to follow the advice and tips above!","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1,"offset":2092},"end":{"line":23,"column":180,"offset":2271}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1,"offset":2092},"end":{"line":23,"column":180,"offset":2271}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here are helpful posts on safety written by our solo female travel experts:","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":2273},"end":{"line":25,"column":76,"offset":2348}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1,"offset":2273},"end":{"line":25,"column":76,"offset":2348}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[],"position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1,"offset":2350},"end":{"line":27,"column":3,"offset":2352}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element"